EPUB TTS was created by Patrick Clark.

Author and creator
  Patrick Clark wrote this software, and rewrote it, over many years. The
  reader, the voice library he auditioned by hand, the markup he invented
  for narration and dialogue, and the long-accumulated rules for reading
  prose aloud well are all his.

Stewardship
  After Patrick passed away in June 2026, his family gathered the copies he
  left behind, pieced them back into a single working whole, repaired what
  had broken with time, finished a few things that were close to done, and
  prepared it so others can read the code and run it themselves. This was
  done with a light touch, in keeping with how he built it.

  Maintained by his family at Black & Tan Labs
  https://github.com/blackandtanlabs
